WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:02.940 --> 00:00:04.740
What happened to her?

3
00:00:04.740 --> 00:00:06.600
Well, she just suddenly collapsed...

4
00:00:06.600 --> 00:00:07.710
What on earth?

5
00:00:07.710 --> 00:00:10.290
Did she faint from some sort of condition?

6
00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:16.270
Huh?!

7
00:00:16.940 --> 00:00:19.680
You're the one who visits 
our store all the time.

8
00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:20.790
What's wrong?

9
00:00:21.770 --> 00:00:23.170
Ah, I'm a huge idiot!

10
00:00:23.170 --> 00:00:25.830
I ended up back here after doing 
nothing but part-time work again!

11
00:00:25.830 --> 00:00:27.600
If I showed them the drawings on my tablet,

12
00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:31.650
I'm sure they'd ask me to make a 
game with me as head illustrator!

13
00:00:31.650 --> 00:00:35.390
I'm not cut out to be a protag at all!

14
00:00:39.820 --> 00:00:42.240
Next time for sure!

15
00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:48.650
I-I didn't realize she was so unstable.

16
00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:53.170
<i>I still have a chance!</i>

17
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:56.020
<i>Good things come in threes!</i>

18
00:00:57.110 --> 00:00:59.780
<i>I know I can return to the past again!</i>

19
00:01:08.090 --> 00:01:13.350
16bit Sensation:
Another Layer

20
00:02:23.540 --> 00:02:25.710
16bit Sensation:
Another Layer

21
00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:35.010
"Good Things Come in Threes!"

22
00:02:39.510 --> 00:02:42.270
<i>The games I got from that granny's shop...</i>

23
00:02:42.670 --> 00:02:45.800
<i>Both times I opened the boxes, 
I was sent back into the past.</i>

24
00:02:47.220 --> 00:02:52.260
<i>The first date was before Christmas 1992,</i>

25
00:02:52.260 --> 00:02:53.740
<i>and the second date was...</i>

26
00:02:54.340 --> 00:02:59.340
<i>the day </i>Kizuato<i> came out: July 26, 1996.</i>

27
00:02:59.700 --> 00:03:02.090
<i>The release date for </i>Doukyuusei<i> was...</i>

28
00:03:02.090 --> 00:03:05.700
<i>December 17, 1992!</i>

29
00:03:05.700 --> 00:03:07.260
I knew it!

30
00:03:07.260 --> 00:03:09.870
I'm going back to the day that 
the game I open came out!

31
00:03:09.870 --> 00:03:12.780
And whenever I open a 
package, it disappears!

32
00:03:12.780 --> 00:03:14.290
That's right!

33
00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:16.720
That must be how it works!

34
00:03:18.350 --> 00:03:21.930
I should try opening another 
game, just to make sure.

35
00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:27.700
<i>I should pick a game that's as close as 
possible to when I went back before.</i>

36
00:03:38.330 --> 00:03:39.240
There!

37
00:03:50.770 --> 00:03:54.240
I can't travel back in time 
with just any ordinary game.

38
00:03:54.240 --> 00:03:57.340
<i>It has to be a game from that shop...</i>

39
00:04:01.610 --> 00:04:04.510
<i>Why are there so many games missing?</i>

40
00:04:04.800 --> 00:04:07.370
<i>What games did I have here again?</i>

41
00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:12.360
Could it be that history has changed?!

42
00:04:12.620 --> 00:04:14.980
Is this because of what I did?

43
00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:17.210
Nuh-uh! That can't be it!

44
00:04:17.210 --> 00:04:19.230
That can't be it! No way!

45
00:04:20.470 --> 00:04:24.990
I mean, all I did was work 
part-time for Alcohol Soft!

46
00:04:25.880 --> 00:04:29.680
Seriously, I haven't done a single thing!

47
00:04:30.230 --> 00:04:34.180
But if something I did in 
the past caused this...

48
00:04:41.740 --> 00:04:44.560
Maybe I should just stop...

49
00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:45.650
It's all too...

50
00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:02.650
Blue Bell

51
00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:16.500
<i>I'm so sick of my job...</i>

52
00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:17.900
No, no!

53
00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:19.450
I wanna go back to Alcohol Soft!

54
00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:22.740
I wanna see everyone from 
Alcohol Soft again!

55
00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:31.260
<i>Maybe one more time wouldn't hurt...</i>

56
00:05:31.780 --> 00:05:33.010
<i>I get it now!</i>

57
00:05:33.010 --> 00:05:34.070
<i>I won't do anything!</i>

58
00:05:34.730 --> 00:05:38.610
<i>I'll lay nice and low, like 
a fugitive on the run!</i>

59
00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:43.130
<i>I bet it's just coincidence 
that my games went missing!</i>

60
00:05:43.130 --> 00:05:44.240
<i>That's right!</i>

61
00:05:44.240 --> 00:05:47.050
<i>It must have been a burglar 
who only steals eroge!</i>

62
00:05:47.050 --> 00:05:49.190
<i>I'll just lay low this time around!</i>

63
00:05:53.950 --> 00:05:57.830
<i>The game closest to when 
I went back last time...</i>

64
00:05:58.560 --> 00:05:59.750
<i>This one?</i>

65
00:05:59.750 --> 00:06:05.740
Kanon<i>, released on June 4, 1999!</i>

66
00:06:09.510 --> 00:06:11.230
Uguu!

67
00:06:29.630 --> 00:06:32.470
<i>There's one month left until July,</i>

68
00:06:30.860 --> 00:06:34.370
Nostradamus's "prophecy of the end of mankind"
Everybody's reactions, one month before July 1999

69
00:06:30.860 --> 00:06:34.370
In the seventh month of
1999, a great King of Terror 
will come from the sky

70
00:06:32.470 --> 00:06:35.750
<i>when Nostradamus predicted a great 
King of Terror would appear!</i>

71
00:06:35.750 --> 00:06:38.140
<i>The year 1999!</i>

72
00:06:42.830 --> 00:06:44.060
What?!

73
00:06:44.670 --> 00:06:46.810
Alcohol Soft is gone!

74
00:06:47.330 --> 00:06:49.140
Th-This is my company's...

75
00:06:49.410 --> 00:06:51.120
Blue Bell's office building!

76
00:06:51.120 --> 00:06:53.580
Did I fail to go back in time?!

77
00:06:55.760 --> 00:06:57.900
Do you have some business with us?

78
00:06:58.710 --> 00:07:00.930
What? Kono-chan?!

79
00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:03.980
Alcohol Soft

80
00:07:02.330 --> 00:07:03.980
Kao-san!

81
00:07:04.270 --> 00:07:05.570
Kono-chan!

82
00:07:05.570 --> 00:07:06.830
Kaori-san!

83
00:07:06.830 --> 00:07:08.800
You went and disappeared on us again!

84
00:07:08.800 --> 00:07:09.870
Goodness!

85
00:07:09.870 --> 00:07:12.560
You haven't changed a bit, Kono-chan!

86
00:07:12.560 --> 00:07:14.990
It's amazing how you look exactly the same!

87
00:07:14.990 --> 00:07:16.740
What have you been up to?!

88
00:07:16.740 --> 00:07:18.610
U-Um...

89
00:07:18.610 --> 00:07:22.030
Well, you could say I went to 
go get a change of clothes...

90
00:07:23.220 --> 00:07:25.490
Three years to go change clothes?

91
00:07:25.490 --> 00:07:27.960
You sure are a joker.

92
00:07:27.960 --> 00:07:29.550
Wanna work part-time again?

93
00:07:30.490 --> 00:07:34.870
<i>I always make the weirdest appearances, 
but they're welcoming me with open arms!</i>

94
00:07:34.870 --> 00:07:36.110
<i>I'm so happy!</i>

95
00:07:36.110 --> 00:07:38.960
<i>Everyone's so nice here!</i>

96
00:07:40.740 --> 00:07:45.100
Alcohol Soft turned into this huge building?

97
00:07:45.100 --> 00:07:46.430
That's right.

98
00:07:46.430 --> 00:07:48.650
As part of the redevelopment 
here in Akihabara.

99
00:07:49.050 --> 00:07:52.650
Just look at how much space we 
have now in our development room.

100
00:07:52.650 --> 00:07:54.090
Ta-dah!

101
00:07:54.090 --> 00:07:55.500
Game cabinets!

102
00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:58.280
Arcade! It's an arcade!

103
00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:01.240
All of it is thanks to 
our game becoming a hit!

104
00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:07.250
Do you
remember
that star?

105
00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:07.250
The latest
 Alcohol
 Soft title!

106
00:08:01.780 --> 00:08:04.950
You know, the game you 
helped us make, <i>Horoscope</i>!

107
00:08:04.950 --> 00:08:07.240
We ended up selling over 100,000 copies!

108
00:08:07.240 --> 00:08:10.340
We released a sequel 
as well as a fandisc...

109
00:08:10.340 --> 00:08:12.970
I never thought we'd put out a fandisc!

110
00:08:12.970 --> 00:08:14.890
Booyah!

111
00:08:15.160 --> 00:08:17.750
We hired more people as well!

112
00:08:17.750 --> 00:08:19.600
I'm Hashimoto, in charge of marketing.

113
00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:21.800
I also manage the fan club.

114
00:08:22.040 --> 00:08:25.030
I'm Kikiko, scenario writer!

115
00:08:25.030 --> 00:08:26.470
I'm Lalako!

116
00:08:26.470 --> 00:08:27.720
We're twins!

117
00:08:27.720 --> 00:08:29.170
Are those your real names?

118
00:08:29.170 --> 00:08:31.160
They're our pen names!

119
00:08:31.160 --> 00:08:33.440
My real name is Senri Koyama.

120
00:08:33.440 --> 00:08:34.500
Mine is Mari.

121
00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:36.300
Call us Kikilala!

122
00:08:36.940 --> 00:08:38.980
We're not done yet!

123
00:08:38.980 --> 00:08:41.580
I'm Yuki, on the graphics team.

124
00:08:41.580 --> 00:08:42.760
I'm Kamiyama.

125
00:08:42.760 --> 00:08:44.000
I'm Minamizato.

126
00:08:44.360 --> 00:08:46.130
I'm Haruhiko, in charge of music.

127
00:08:47.380 --> 00:08:51.590
So is she the legendary 
phantom staff member?

128
00:08:51.590 --> 00:08:52.760
That's right.

129
00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:57.480
Kono-chan is a mysterious graphic artist 
who shows up once every few years.

130
00:08:57.480 --> 00:09:00.530
She may not look it, but she's a 
real veteran here at this company!

131
00:09:00.530 --> 00:09:01.930
Isn't that right, Kono-chan?

132
00:09:01.930 --> 00:09:04.090
Th-That's right!

133
00:09:04.090 --> 00:09:07.390
I may not look it, but I'm a real 
veteran here at this company!

134
00:09:09.390 --> 00:09:10.680
Ahem!

135
00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:11.810
Let me introduce myself.

136
00:09:11.810 --> 00:09:13.350
My name is Konoha Akisato!

137
00:09:13.350 --> 00:09:15.950
My favorite food is anything sweet!

138
00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:20.170
My specialty is doing impressions of 
a VTuber reading off Super Chats!

139
00:09:20.170 --> 00:09:22.610
Wow! Thanks, everyone!

140
00:09:22.610 --> 00:09:24.050
It's nice to meet all of you!

141
00:09:25.400 --> 00:09:28.210
I-It's nice to meet you.

142
00:09:28.540 --> 00:09:34.050
And back there, feeling totally out of place, 
is our veteran old-timer staff member!

143
00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:35.540
Who're you calling an old-timer?

144
00:09:40.770 --> 00:09:42.410
M-Mamoru-kun...

145
00:09:42.410 --> 00:09:44.120
H-Hey there.

146
00:09:47.220 --> 00:09:50.650
R-Rocking the glasses look, huh?

147
00:09:51.370 --> 00:09:54.170
<i>Mamoru-kun's looking even older now!</i>

148
00:09:54.170 --> 00:09:55.730
<i>And way scarier to boot!</i>

149
00:09:55.990 --> 00:09:58.340
How many times are you going 
to show up like this?

150
00:09:58.340 --> 00:09:59.210
Huh?

151
00:09:59.210 --> 00:10:00.900
Vanishing out of the blue like you did,

152
00:10:00.900 --> 00:10:02.660
only to show up again, out of the blue.

153
00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:05.010
At least tell me how it all works.

154
00:10:05.010 --> 00:10:06.970
Y-You see, Mamoru-kun...

155
00:10:06.970 --> 00:10:08.690
I figured it out!

156
00:10:08.690 --> 00:10:10.680
How the time travel works!

157
00:10:11.280 --> 00:10:12.330
What?

158
00:10:12.740 --> 00:10:15.700
See, when I open up a game...

159
00:10:15.700 --> 00:10:16.600
A game?

160
00:10:25.280 --> 00:10:27.400
How's it hangin'?!

161
00:10:27.400 --> 00:10:29.710
You folks better not be goofing off!

162
00:10:29.710 --> 00:10:31.160
Manager!

163
00:10:31.160 --> 00:10:34.390
The only one goofing off here is you!

164
00:10:34.390 --> 00:10:36.450
You're always out of the office partying!

165
00:10:36.770 --> 00:10:39.380
Just look at that awful getup!

166
00:10:39.380 --> 00:10:43.570
The spitting image of a president 
who's suddenly got cash to burn.

167
00:10:43.570 --> 00:10:46.670
Whoa, harsh words there, missy!

168
00:10:46.670 --> 00:10:49.700
But I've got just the thing to shut you up!

169
00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:51.540
Hear me out, Kaori!

170
00:10:51.540 --> 00:10:54.960
I'm about to say something amazing!

171
00:10:54.960 --> 00:10:56.240
What is it?

172
00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:58.960
Spare us the theatrics 
and spit it out already!

173
00:11:01.740 --> 00:11:03.880
Our game...

174
00:11:12.460 --> 00:11:14.270
is going to be released on console!

175
00:11:17.920 --> 00:11:21.090
What?! On console?!

176
00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:24.410
Alcohol Soft

177
00:11:24.030 --> 00:11:26.420
C-Console...

178
00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:28.990
Don't give me that nonsense!

179
00:11:28.990 --> 00:11:31.480
I'm not joking here!

180
00:11:31.480 --> 00:11:32.950
Take it away, Gaya-san!

181
00:11:35.150 --> 00:11:36.510
Heya!

182
00:11:36.510 --> 00:11:39.430
I'm Ichigaya, from Diamond Studio!

183
00:11:39.430 --> 00:11:40.750
What?!

184
00:11:40.750 --> 00:11:43.550
Wait, by Ichigaya, do you mean 
the one and only Ichigaya-san?!

185
00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:49.430
Hit-Maker Special Feature

186
00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:49.430
Hit-Maker Special F

187
00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:49.430
On the History and Future of Games
Fire Dragon...
Genius Producer
Ichigaya...

188
00:11:43.550 --> 00:11:45.800
He created the <i>Fire Dragon</i> series!

189
00:11:45.800 --> 00:11:47.280
Even <i>I've</i> heard of him!

190
00:11:47.280 --> 00:11:49.430
I've spent so much time on those games!

191
00:11:49.430 --> 00:11:50.820
Wow!

192
00:11:50.820 --> 00:11:52.030
A celebrity!

193
00:11:52.030 --> 00:11:53.850
What's he doing here?

194
00:11:54.080 --> 00:11:56.510
Mamoru-kun, who's that?

195
00:11:56.510 --> 00:11:58.620
I vaguely recall that name.

196
00:11:58.620 --> 00:12:02.330
I've been a long time fan of Alcohol Soft!

197
00:12:02.330 --> 00:12:04.530
I played your latest game, <i>Horoscope</i>.

198
00:12:04.530 --> 00:12:06.000
It was wonderful!

199
00:12:06.320 --> 00:12:08.760
I can just see it now!

200
00:12:08.760 --> 00:12:12.170
We're about to enter the age of bishojo!

201
00:12:12.170 --> 00:12:16.050
Console ports of bishojo games have 
been thriving for a while now!

202
00:12:16.050 --> 00:12:17.750
<i>The Mystery of Nonomura Hospital</i>!

203
00:12:17.750 --> 00:12:19.790
<i>Doukyuusei</i>! <i>Kakyuusei</i>!

204
00:12:19.790 --> 00:12:20.590
<i>YU-NO</i>!

205
00:12:20.590 --> 00:12:22.560
<i>Can Can Bunny Premiere 2</i>!

206
00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:23.880
They've all been hits!

207
00:12:23.880 --> 00:12:24.960
However!

208
00:12:25.230 --> 00:12:28.920
The morons in the industry have been 
turning a blind eye to that fact!

209
00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:33.600
Refusing to acknowledge bishojo while 
using them to rake in the cash!

210
00:12:33.930 --> 00:12:35.820
You may be right.

211
00:12:35.820 --> 00:12:38.770
There are a lot of folks who 
are ashamed of bishojo.

212
00:12:38.770 --> 00:12:40.490
However!

213
00:12:40.490 --> 00:12:41.770
The times are changing!

214
00:12:41.770 --> 00:12:46.630
In this economic recession, bishojo 
are the one thing continuing to grow!

215
00:12:46.630 --> 00:12:47.780
They're booming like crazy!

216
00:12:47.780 --> 00:12:52.260
The biggest genre of the 21st 
century is going to be bishojo!

217
00:12:52.260 --> 00:12:54.040
I guarantee it!

218
00:12:54.040 --> 00:12:59.340
We at Diamond Studio have a proven 
record of porting games over to console.

219
00:12:59.340 --> 00:13:04.720
Won't you trust us with producing the 
port of Alcohol Soft's <i>Horoscope</i>?

220
00:13:04.720 --> 00:13:09.470
It'll be a masterpiece that surpasses 
the console version of <i>To Heart</i>!

221
00:13:09.470 --> 00:13:12.860
Everyone from Alcohol Soft, 
let us join hands...

222
00:13:13.110 --> 00:13:15.070
Gaya-san!

223
00:13:13.510 --> 00:13:16.730
And start a worldwide revolution!

224
00:13:16.730 --> 00:13:18.190
That's all from me!

225
00:13:20.360 --> 00:13:21.690
Well? Well?

226
00:13:21.690 --> 00:13:23.100
Isn't it amazing?

227
00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:24.460
The famous Ichigaya!

228
00:13:24.460 --> 00:13:25.780
What a surprise!

229
00:13:25.780 --> 00:13:28.330
I had no idea you knew a celebrity like him!

230
00:13:28.330 --> 00:13:31.180
Well... I guess it was a little surprising.

231
00:13:31.180 --> 00:13:34.100
I wasn't just drinking myself 
silly for nothing out there!

232
00:13:34.100 --> 00:13:36.170
I'm expanding my network every day!

233
00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:38.450
You'll say yes to the port, right?

234
00:13:38.450 --> 00:13:39.680
I'm all for it!

235
00:13:39.680 --> 00:13:43.180
Well, there doesn't seem 
to be any downside for us.

236
00:13:43.180 --> 00:13:44.940
Sure, why not.

237
00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:46.520
Wow! Amazing!

238
00:13:46.520 --> 00:13:49.560
We're gonna go mainstream with this!

239
00:13:49.560 --> 00:13:51.330
A console game!

240
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:52.590
Wow!

241
00:13:52.590 --> 00:13:54.480
I wonder what platform they'll target!

242
00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:55.830
Kono-chan!

243
00:13:55.830 --> 00:13:57.120
Meiko-san!

244
00:13:57.120 --> 00:13:58.060
We did it!

245
00:13:58.060 --> 00:14:00.500
A console game! Console!

246
00:14:00.500 --> 00:14:01.780
It's like I'm in a dream!

247
00:14:01.780 --> 00:14:03.560
You're not dreaming!

248
00:14:03.560 --> 00:14:04.810
It is my dream, though!

249
00:14:04.810 --> 00:14:06.640
It wasn't just a dream!

250
00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:13.320
And so, when I open up one of these 
games, I travel back in time.

251
00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:15.900
Not that I know why it happens.

252
00:14:15.900 --> 00:14:18.830
And you end up on the day 
that the game was released?

253
00:14:19.350 --> 00:14:21.210
Mamoru-kun, do you know how it works?

254
00:14:21.210 --> 00:14:22.900
How the hell would I?

255
00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:25.520
Maybe I should try opening another one.

256
00:14:26.260 --> 00:14:27.370
Stop it!

257
00:14:27.370 --> 00:14:29.770
What if it sends you back further in time?

258
00:14:29.770 --> 00:14:31.760
Y-You're right...

259
00:14:34.470 --> 00:14:36.100
U-Um...

260
00:14:36.460 --> 00:14:39.150
Um, like, you see...

261
00:14:39.150 --> 00:14:41.560
There's one teensy thing that's weird.

262
00:14:41.560 --> 00:14:42.680
What is it?

263
00:14:43.760 --> 00:14:45.490
Every time I go back,

264
00:14:46.760 --> 00:14:50.150
there are games missing from my place.

265
00:14:50.150 --> 00:14:51.980
My eroge.

266
00:14:53.180 --> 00:14:55.870
Do you mean they disappeared?

267
00:14:55.870 --> 00:14:59.180
I-It's probably just a burglar 
who only steals eroge!

268
00:14:59.180 --> 00:15:01.830
Are there burglars like that in the future?

269
00:15:01.830 --> 00:15:03.490
N-Not really...

270
00:15:03.490 --> 00:15:04.390
Then don't mention it!

271
00:15:04.390 --> 00:15:09.590
M-Maybe I've been changing history...

272
00:15:09.590 --> 00:15:10.520
The possibility...

273
00:15:11.390 --> 00:15:13.770
made me a little bit scared.

274
00:15:14.570 --> 00:15:17.990
Hey, weren't you the one who told me

275
00:15:17.990 --> 00:15:19.800
that it's okay to change history?

276
00:15:20.260 --> 00:15:22.770
M-Maybe I did...

277
00:15:22.770 --> 00:15:24.770
What was the point of that, then?!

278
00:15:24.770 --> 00:15:29.860
W-Well, seeing those games disappear 
right off my shelf took me by surprise.

279
00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:33.340
I mean, I'm sure it's totally unrelated!

280
00:15:33.340 --> 00:15:36.480
Well, I'm sure you wouldn't get it!

281
00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:39.650
Guess you could call it 
a time traveler problem.

282
00:15:39.650 --> 00:15:41.420
You really get on my nerves.

283
00:15:41.910 --> 00:15:44.000
In that case, why did you come here?

284
00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:44.790
Huh?

285
00:15:45.050 --> 00:15:48.880
If you don't want to change 
history, why did you come here?

286
00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:51.100
Th-That's because...

287
00:15:51.570 --> 00:15:54.720
I-I wanted to meet the people here!

288
00:15:54.720 --> 00:15:57.220
Everyone at Alcohol Soft!

289
00:15:57.450 --> 00:16:01.230
The truth is, I came here because 
I wanted to make a game!

290
00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:02.660
Same goes for last time!

291
00:16:02.660 --> 00:16:04.860
But it's fine now if I don't get to!

292
00:16:04.860 --> 00:16:06.200
I'm trying to behave myself!

293
00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:09.200
I won't change history, and I don't 
mind if all I do is part-time work!

294
00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:10.580
I won't even talk to anyone!

295
00:16:10.580 --> 00:16:12.370
There's no way you can pull that off.

296
00:16:12.370 --> 00:16:14.130
Whoa!

297
00:16:14.130 --> 00:16:17.200
You think I'm just a big, fat wimp!

298
00:16:17.200 --> 00:16:19.320
That's wimp discrimination!

299
00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:21.210
It's impossible.

300
00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:23.330
Besides, what's the point in doing that?

301
00:16:23.330 --> 00:16:25.590
What exactly did you come here to do?

302
00:16:27.420 --> 00:16:29.470
W-Well...

303
00:16:33.330 --> 00:16:38.350
Okay, let's decide on what everyone 
will be doing for the console port.

304
00:16:33.340 --> 00:16:35.930
Conference Room

305
00:16:33.340 --> 00:16:35.930
Occupied

306
00:16:38.930 --> 00:16:41.390
Kaori
Director

307
00:16:39.140 --> 00:16:42.320
I'll be the director...

308
00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:47.060
The director of a console game!

309
00:16:47.060 --> 00:16:51.070
Next, Mei-chan will do the 
designs for two new characters.

310
00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:52.680
Sure thing!

311
00:16:53.410 --> 00:16:55.360
How nerve-wracking...

312
00:16:55.360 --> 00:16:59.430
Hey, how come I'm not in 
charge of the new scenarios?

313
00:16:59.430 --> 00:17:01.780
I did the original scenario for this game!

314
00:17:01.790 --> 00:17:12.550
Kaori - Director
Meiko - Character Designs
Kikilala...

315
00:17:02.040 --> 00:17:05.140
I know you'll add in sex scenes, so no way!

316
00:17:05.140 --> 00:17:08.170
You focus on fixing up the main scenario!

317
00:17:08.170 --> 00:17:12.550
The new story segments will 
be left to Kikilala-chan!

318
00:17:12.550 --> 00:17:14.010
'Kay!

319
00:17:14.290 --> 00:17:16.940
They're our writers for all-ages content!

320
00:17:16.940 --> 00:17:18.660
How wishy-washy!

321
00:17:22.930 --> 00:17:24.290
Mamocchi.

322
00:17:24.290 --> 00:17:26.850
You'll handle the system, won't you?

323
00:17:29.100 --> 00:17:30.390
Mamocchi!

324
00:17:30.390 --> 00:17:31.410
Are you paying attention?

325
00:17:32.020 --> 00:17:33.980
Y-Yeah, got it.

326
00:17:33.980 --> 00:17:36.970
Diamond will be lending us a 
specialized development kit,

327
00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:38.410
so I don't foresee any problems.

328
00:17:38.410 --> 00:17:41.040
You're not going to be developing 
on a DOS/V machine?

329
00:17:41.040 --> 00:17:43.350
It's finally time for you 
to make your debut, huh?

330
00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:45.490
I'll be working on a PC-98, of course.

331
00:17:45.490 --> 00:17:47.920
Also, for a console release,

332
00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:50.230
we'll need to make an animated opening,

333
00:17:50.230 --> 00:17:52.910
and hire voice actresses 
to voice the characters...

334
00:17:52.910 --> 00:17:54.450
Um, Konoha-san.

335
00:17:54.450 --> 00:17:57.050
You're really okay with performing 
chores as a part-timer?

336
00:17:57.050 --> 00:17:58.090
Yes!

337
00:17:58.090 --> 00:18:00.390
Just let me know if you 
have any errands for me!

338
00:18:00.680 --> 00:18:02.970
Why are you whispering?

339
00:18:02.970 --> 00:18:05.110
Oh, don't mind me!

340
00:18:05.110 --> 00:18:08.090
I'm just trying to influence 
things as little as possible!

341
00:18:08.090 --> 00:18:09.130
Influence?

342
00:18:09.130 --> 00:18:12.370
Okay, I think that covers 
it for today's meeting!

343
00:18:14.280 --> 00:18:15.250
Kono-chan?

344
00:18:15.490 --> 00:18:17.620
Why do you have a mop?

345
00:18:17.620 --> 00:18:21.270
Konoha-san insisted strongly on 
being assigned to cleaning duty.

346
00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:22.440
That's right.

347
00:18:22.440 --> 00:18:23.400
Why?

348
00:18:23.400 --> 00:18:25.540
We've got plenty of 
illustration work for you.

349
00:18:25.850 --> 00:18:27.880
Well, it's just for this once...

350
00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:39.010
How should the additional characters look?

351
00:18:39.010 --> 00:18:41.250
Let me think...

352
00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:42.900
Kyonshi-san!

353
00:18:42.900 --> 00:18:44.750
Please give it some proper thought!

354
00:18:45.010 --> 00:18:46.750
I'm thinking!

355
00:18:46.750 --> 00:18:47.540
Hurry!

356
00:18:47.540 --> 00:18:48.280
Yeah, yeah.

357
00:18:48.280 --> 00:18:49.640
One "yes" will do!

358
00:18:49.640 --> 00:18:50.880
Yeah, yeah...

359
00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:53.550
This is nice...

360
00:18:55.480 --> 00:18:56.990
